name: Sweetwater Community Nursing Services
notes: Both Pfizer and J&J vaccine are available on a walk-in basis, no appointment necessary. If you do not schedule online we will help you register when you come to the office.  If you are scheduling a second dose of Pfizer, it has to be at least 17 days since your first dose, preferably closer to 21 days.  J&J vaccine does NOT require a second dose.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Fremont County Public Health-Riverton
notes: Please wear short sleeved shirts and expect to be observed for 15 minutes after your injection. If you have any anaphylactic allergies requiring use of an epi-pen in the past we will be unable to give you a vaccine, you will need to get your vaccine in a clinic or hospital. If you have any questions please call our office at 856-6979, Thank You!
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
